Restore people's preferred social media links

For some reason, Twitter is giving me 500s when I try to load profiles.
While working on #42, I wrongly assumed that these Twitter accounts were
no longer active and therefore made all of the profiles link to GitHub.
It turns out the profiles do exist, so we can link to them after all.

Use two-space indents consistently in source files

While working on #42, I noticed that some of the spacing in index.html
was inconsistent, making it hard for me to modify the source without
getting confused. This commit introduces a consistent two-space indent
stipulated by .editorconfig.

Development docs: "npm run test" => "npm test"

Pass audit even if some modules require updates

The audit is intended to notify developers about any modules with
security vulnerabilities. Most can be updated, but some cannot. When
there are modules that cannot be updated, there's really not much that
can be done about it, so we don't want to fail the whole "npm test"
command as a result.
Add post-test "npm audit", fix errors

Revert "Switch from NPM to Yarn"

This reverts commit 0449c6b8da659388a5243d00ea1a4a94d983cbde. It seems
that the referenced issue [1] may have been fixed since I last checked.

[1] https://github.com/npm/npm/issues/16839

Switch from NPM to Yarn

Lockfiles are great. We should use them whenever possible.
Unfortunately, due to an unresolved issue that is apparently difficult
to reproduce, the presence of package-lock.json occasionally causes npm
not to install some dependencies.

This hasn't been an issue on this project yet, but it has caused several
Heroku builds to fail on other projects.

More information:
https://github.com/npm/npm/issues/16839

probably don't care whether Greenkeeper is enabled.
